Absolutely. While **EME-GIR** (CuneiScript) looks like an ancient text, its under-the-hood logic is perfectly suited for complex, modern software architecture. In fact, because Sumerian grammar is inherently structural and relational, it excels at things like **Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)**, **asynchronous operations**, and **state management**.

To prove it, let’s scale up the language to handle advanced computing concepts like **Classes, Inheritance, and Recursion.**

